description:
1992 Mercedes Benz 500E W124, Wolf in Sheeps Clothing. Available now is this gorgeous Euro 92 Mercedes Benz 500e. 
Made famous by the fact that these cars were so wide they didnt fit the Mercedes assembly line at the time the company decided to send each one to Porsche to be hand built in their factory. The widened arches on the front and rear fenders gave the 500e an incredible street presence and a timeless body style that was universally loved by car enthusiasts and the general world population. Our car is a euro model built for the Japanese market.
name: E500 Limited W124

description:
1997 Mazda FD3S RX7 Single Turbo.
Available now is this beautiful JDM 97 FD Rx7. Refinished in championship yellow this car looks great in photos but even better in person. Body of the car is in great shape with straight bodylines and even gaps throughout. Tasteful and period correct aero modifications consist of a Mazda speed rear spoiler, RE Ameyiya side skirts and 99spec Front bumper. Pop up headlights work as they should and go up and down evenly with the lights on or off. HID kit is a expensive bellof kit. The height of the car has been lowered a bit to reduce body roll and to take advantage of the great riding HKS Hipermax coil over suspension. The height is perfect it doesnâ€™t rub on any tire and the ride is firm but comfortable. The white Advan racing RC3 super tarmac wheels show nicely and wrapped in Bridgestone tires on all 4 wheels. Bottom of the car is very clean, frame rails are straight there is no rust of signs of accidents.
name: RX7 FD3S

description:
1996 Ferrari 355 Berlinetta Challenge plus. 
With over one hundred thousand dollars in receipts this 355 has been built to a spec that few builds ever achieve. The shop that spearheaded the project was Accel Engine Development Office out of Yokohama, with the intent to increase the durability of the stereotypically fragile Ferrari to allow it to run at the pace of air cooled Porsches on the circuit. The result of these modifications is what we like to call a 355 challenge plus. Since the recent refresh was completed only 1500km have been accrued.
name: F355 Berlinetta

description: The Porsche 911 GT3 RS Coupe is a high-performance sports car known for its speed, precision, and racing-inspired design. With a lightweight build, aerodynamic features, and a powerful engine, it delivers thrilling performance on both the track and the road. Inside, it offers a racing-inspired interior with advanced technology and precise handling. It`s a dream car for those seeking the ultimate combination of style and performance.
name: 911 GT3 RS

description:
Audi RS6 Avant.
If you like fast wagons like I do, then you'll agree that the Audi RS6 Avant is one of the coolest wagons ever to grace U.S. shores. It boasts supercar levels of performance while wearing a very practical body that also happens to look beautiful and menacing at the same time and the massively powerful twin-turbo V8 helps, too. This particular RS6 Avant touts an impressive list of factory equipment, including the Executive, Black Optic, and Driver Assistance packages plus, it's finished in handsome Daytona Gray Pearl, which looks fantastic paired with the Cognac interior. It also features some neat modifications, including an XPEL Stealth exterior wrap, a Milltek exhaust, and a Cete suspension controller. This RS6 also comes with a clean, accident-free Carfax report, for added peace of mind.
name: RS6 Avant

description: This is a 2022 BMW M3, finished in Isle of Man Green Metallic with a black interior. This BMW is equipped with the desirable 6-speed manual transmission, and the odometer currently displays approximately 3,500 miles. The attached Carfax vehicle history report shows no accidents or mileage discrepancies in this BMW's past. It also confirms that it has been registered by one owner since new. A window sticker is provided in the photo gallery, and a partial list of notable equipment includes the BMW Connected Package Pro, 19-inch front and 20-inch rear Style 826 M Performance wheels, Adaptive M suspension, an M Sport differential, extended Merino leather upholstery, power-adjustable, heated, and ventilated M Sport front seats, and more as detailed below. Modifications reported by the seller are limited to tinted windows.
name: M3

description: The Mercedes-Benz G63 AMG is an iconic off-roader with shocking performance, thanks to AMGs amazing 536-horsepower twin-turbocharged V8 and trademark G-Class qualities like 4-wheel drive with triple locking differentials and a sturdy ladder frame chassis. This particular G63 AMG ticks a lot of boxes, as it boasts a long list of impressive factory equipment including the Designo Exclusive Leather, Exterior Stainless Steel, and Seat Comfort packages. Plus, this G63 is mostly unmodified and its offered with a clean, accident-free Carfax report for added buyer confidence.
name: G63 AMG

description: Porsche 935

The Mercedes-AMG C63 is a thrilling coupe with a potent turbocharged V8, a luxurious interior, and beautiful styling and its also the final C63 with a V8, which makes it particularly special. This C63 S is finished in striking Polar White, and it comes equipped with some desirable options including the AMG Night, Driver Assistance, Multimedia, and Memory packages along with Nappa leather upholstery and a high-end Burmester sound system. This C63 also boasts some tasteful upgrades, like a RENNtech ECU tune and a RENNtech valved exhaust control module, that further enhance its performance and sound.
name: AMG C63 S Coupe

description: This 2022 BMW M5 CS is finished in Frozen Brands Hatch Gray Metallic over black Merino leather and Alcantara upholstery and is powered by a twin-turbocharged 4.4-liter V8 mated to a ZF eight-speed automatic transmission and an M xDrive all-wheel-drive system. Additional equipment includes the Competition and M Drivers packages along with 20 Style 789 wheels, an M Sport exhaust system, carbon-ceramic brakes, a carbon-fiber engine cover, heated M Carbon front bucket seats, remote engine start, Live Cockpit Pro, navigation, and a Harman Kardon surround sound system. The car was originally delivered to BMW of El Cajon in California and was acquired by the seller in May 2022.
name: M5 CS

description: The original Audi R8 is a great option if you're in the market for your first supercar, as it offers exotic styling, thrilling performance, and relative reliability. This example ticks many of the right boxes: It boasts under 11,000 miles, it's unmodified, AND it's the V10-powered model, boosting horsepower significantly over the standard V8. This R8 also touts some great equipment, including the Magnetic Ride suspension system and Carbon Sigma interior trim, and the Quattro all-wheel drive system increases grip while providing peace of mind on winter roads.
name: R8 V10 Spyder

description: The Audi S5 Sportback is a thrilling blend of performance and practicality, boasting a potent 354-hp turbocharged V6 and the surefootedness of Audi's Quattro all-wheel drive system. This particular S5 Sportback is especially appealing, as it comes completely unmodified and features the Prestige and S Sport packages for enhanced luxury and performance. This S5 also touts some great factory equipment like 19-inch wheels, a power sunroof, leather and Alcantara upholstery, and Carbon Atlas inlays. Plus, this S5 is offered with a clean, accident-free Carfax report showing warm-climate Texas ownership since new, along with a recent Lemon Squad pre-purchase inspection, for added peace of mind.
name: S5 Sportback

description: The Porsche Macan S is a thrilling blend of sports car performance and SUV practicality, boasting a potent turbocharged V6 and all-wheel drive for a driving experience that's shockingly fun compared to many luxury crossovers. This particular Macan S is finished in a gorgeous Night Blue Metallic, and it touts some desirable options like the Premium Package Plus, 21-inch RS Spyder Design wheels, a panoramic roof system, and more. This Macan S is also completely unmodified and it boasts with a clean, accident-free Carfax report, adding to the peace of mind for its next owner.
name: Macan S

description: This 1996 Nissan Skyline GTR R33 is a prime example of the tuning arms race that took place in Japan in the 90s. This famous A'PEXI Demo car set multiple records on closed courses with its 1000BHP RB26 with the rev limiter increased to 9500RPM all going to a HKS 6-Speed Dogbox transmission sitting on authentic BBS LM wheels
name: Skyline GTR R33

description: Born as a 1996 Porsche 993 Turbo in Speed Yellow with Sunroof Delete, this RoW car was owned by ARx Corp in Japan meticulously and very carefully built into a colossal track eating, street legal precision machine and an $800K build in 2022 money including the car. There isnt a new resto mod Porsche today that could even compare from looks and performance. If you are looking for the purest form of adrenaline look no further. This will propel you cross country, endurance track day or grocery getting. Suspension and steering are perfectly balanced for precise handling and almost effortless cornering. It will just go wherever you point the steering wheel to.  Switchable electric power steering is just a phenomenal addition that I wish I would have had back in the 90s.
name: 911 Turbo GT2 Spec

description: This 1995 Audi RS2 is a left-hand-drive example that previously resided in Japan and was imported to Canada in 2014. It was acquired four years ago in Quebec by the seller, who has added 6k of the 150k kilometers (~93k miles) shown. The car is finished in RS Blue over a black leather interior, and is one of 2,981 built during a 16-month production run from 1994 to 1995. Power is provided by a turbocharged 20-valve 2.2L inline-five mated to a six-speed manual gearbox and Quattro all-wheel drive.
name: RS2 Avant

description: This 2016 Chevrolet Corvette Z06 coupe is one of 500 C7.R Edition examples produced for the US market and was designed as a homage to Corvette Racing C7.R race cars. The car is powered by a supercharged 6.2-liter LT4 V8 linked with an eight-speed automatic gearbox and an electronic limited-slip differential, and it is finished in Corvette Racing Yellow over black leather and sueded microfiber upholstery.
name: Corvette Z06 Coupe

description: The E39 BMW M5 is a true BMW icon, boasting great handling and handsome styling, along with a potent V8 paired with a mandatory 6-speed manual transmission. This particular M5 is finished in a classic black-on-black color combination and looks to be in great condition. It also boasts some nice factory equipment, like full Nappa leather upholstery, heated front seats, and those beautiful Style 65 wheels. Its also mostly unmodified, with tinted windows being the only change from stock and its offered with a clean, accident-free Carfax report, further adding to the appeal
name: M5

description: The 991 Porsche 911 Turbo is a thrilling sports car with supercar-baiting performance thanks to a powerful twin-turbo flat-6 engine, a clever all-wheel drive system, and a quick-shifting dual-clutch transmission. This particular 911 Turbo boasts some nice factory equipment, including a set of 20-inch Turbo S center-lock wheels, a sunroof, and a Bose sound system.
name: 911 Turbo S

description: The R230 Mercedes-Benz SL is becoming a sought-after modern classic and the SL65 AMG is especially desirable, as it boasts a powerful 6.0-liter twin-turbocharged V12 that puts down over 600 horsepower and 738 lb-ft of torque! This particular example has been further enhanced with some nice modifications, including a Kleemann ECU tune for more power, a lowered suspension, 20-inch aftermarket wheels, a carbon fiber rear spoiler, and more.
name: SL65 AMG R230

description: The E70 X5M, as it's a handsome SUV with some truly excellent performance courtesy of an exceptionally muscular 555-horsepower turbocharged V8. This particular X5M looks to be a nice example, touting a few cosmetic modifications and just under 52,000 miles from new, which is reasonably low for one of these. This car also boasts some fantastic equipment, and it's a thrilling SUV to drive that should make the next owner especially happy.
name: X5 M

description: The SEC was the elegant, pillarless coupe version of the W126 Mercedes-Benz S-Class  and it's a lot less common than the sedan! These were tremendously expensive when they were new; you really had to be someone to buy one, and they came loaded with the features buyers expected from a luxury coupe in the 1980s. This particular 560SEC is finished in an attractive Arctic White over gray color combination, and it features some nice equipment like a sunroof, leather upholstery, heated front seats, and automatic climate control plus that big 5.5-liter V8. It also touts an awesome set of ATS AMG Penta wheels, and it benefits from a recent repaint and servicing.
name: 560SEC W126

description: If you're in the market for a do-it-all family car, the Audi Q7 should be on your shopping list it's spacious, it's luxurious, AND it boasts full-time all-wheel-drive. This example touts the 3.0-liter V6, which is a nice upgrade over the 2.0-liter turbocharged 4-cylinder that Audi made standard in 2021, and it benefits from a long list of features including the Prestige, Convenience, and Executive, packages
name: Q7

description: Black 2023 Audi SQ5 Premium Plus quattro quattro 8-Speed Automatic with Tiptronic 3.0L TFSI Recent Arrival!
name: SQ5 Sportback

description: The Audi SQ8 Sportback is likely to feature a dynamic and athletic exterior design, characterized by bold lines, a coupe-like roofline, and signature Audi styling elements. Its sporty appearance is complemented by a performance-oriented chassis and aerodynamic enhancements. Large alloy wheels, a distinctive front grille, and quad exhaust outlets are typical features that enhance its sporty and aggressive presence on the road.
name: SQ8 Quattro

description: The 2022 BMW X5 M epitomizes the convergence of luxury and high-performance in the SUV segment. Boasting an assertive exterior design, this model features distinctive M-specific elements, including a bold front grille, aggressive air intakes, and aerodynamic enhancements. Under the hood, a potent turbocharged V8 engine, likely delivering substantial horsepower and torque, powers the X5 M, complemented by BMW's M xDrive all-wheel-drive system for exceptional traction and performance.
name: X5 M

description: The 2022 BMW X6 M represents the pinnacle of performance and luxury within the SUV segment. Characterized by a distinctive and commanding exterior, the X6 M features signature M-specific design elements, including a bold front grille, aggressive air intakes, and aerodynamic enhancements, creating an imposing presence on the road.
name: X6 M

description: The R129 SL is a modern classic Mercedes-Benz, boasting iconic styling, bank-vault build quality, and a luxurious interior. This particular example is a range-topping SL600, which features the famous M120 V12 engine, a panoramic hardtop, the Sport Package, and really low mileage for one of these. It also boasts a nitrous oxide system and Brembo front brakes.
name: SL600 R129

description: We've established ourselves as the premier sellers of Maybach models on the internet, having sold four already and I'm always happy to get more of these, because they're truly fantastic luxury cars with amazingly supple interiors filled with equipment. This particular example touted a $326,000 sticker price back when it was new.
name: Maybach 57

description: The F12 BMW M6 is a fantastic, sporty convertible that offers thrilling acceleration, a luxurious interior, and handsome styling. This particular M6 touts low mileage, with just 21,000 miles on the odometer, and it's a high-performance Competition model with a 600-horsepower twin-turbocharged V8 under the hood. It's also well equipped with the Executive and Driver Assistance packages, adaptive full LED headlights, and Apple CarPlay compatibility plus, it's unmodified, which is nice to see.
name: M6 Competition

description: The F87 M2 is a fun, exciting, and perfectly-sized sports coupe. This M2 touts several appealing benefits â€” namely a 6-speed manual transmission, relatively low mileage, and a gorgeous Long Beach Blue Metallic exterior color. This M2 is also mostly unmodified, with desirable window tint, paint protection film, and painted front reflectors being the only changes from stock.
name: M2

description: The BMW M4 CS is a thrilling coupe, boasting a more intense driving experience than the standard M4, along with a more powerful turbocharged 6-cylinder engine with 454 horsepower and only 1,000 examples made it to the States, so it's exceptionally rare. This particular M4 CS is finished in the handsome Alpine White, and its mostly unmodified, for added peace of mind. It also touts some great factory equipment, including the Executive package, adaptive M suspension, and a set of cool Style 763 wheels.
name: M4 CS

description: The latest BMW M8 is a thrilling car, boasting gorgeous styling and truly exceptional performance, thanks to a twin-turbocharged V8 with nearly 620 horsepower. This particular example is nearly new, with less than 1,000 miles on the clock. It's also finished in stunning Ametrin Metallic color, and it features some amazing options, like the M Competition, Driving Assistance, and M Carbon Exterior packages.
name: M8 Competition

description: The new Audi R8 is a sensational car, and I think they look fantastic and if the Lamborghini HuracÃ¡n is too flashy for you, then this is the way to go. This particular R8 is a true driver's car ditching Audi's famed Quattro all-wheel drive system for a rear-wheel drive configuration to handle its naturally-aspirated V10. It also touts desirable equipment like the Diamond Quilted Leather Package, a sport exhaust system, and a Bang & Olufsen sound system to further enhance the driving experience.
name: R8 V10 Coupe

description: The Mercedes-AMG GT Black Series is an extremely exciting supercar with tremendous performance, thanks to the motorsport-derived suspension and aero components, backed up by a massively powerful twin-turbocharged V8 that boasts an impressive 720 horsepower. This particular GT Black Series is especially desirable, as it has just 36 miles, making it as close to new as possible and I love how menacing it looks finished in Obsidian Black.
name: AMG GT Black Series

description: The Mercedes-AMG GT 4-door is probably the best-handling 4-door car I've ever driven, and I absolutely love it. It touts fantastic handling and massive power especially in 63 S trim, with a 630 horsepower twin-turbocharged V8 under the hood. This particular GT63 S is finished in a magnificent Designo Selenite Gray Magno over Red Pepper color combination, and it boasts some great equipment like the AMG Aerodynamics, AMG Exterior Carbon Fiber II, and AMG Night Packages, a carbon fiber roof panel, 21-inch AMG wheels, and an AMG performance exhaust system.
name: AMG GT63 S

description: This 2005 Porsche Carrera GT is one of 1,270 examples built during a four-year production run. It was first registered in Ontario, Canada, and later spent time in British Columbia before being acquired by the Mississauga-based selling dealer in early 2023. The car is finished in GT Silver Metallic over Terracotta leather and is powered by a 5.7-liter V10 paired with a six-speed manual transaxle. Equipment includes a limited-slip differential, 19â€³ and 20â€³ center-lock alloy wheels, ceramic composite brakes, an electronically actuated rear spoiler, removable roof panels, xenon headlights, air conditioning, a Porsche Online Pro CD stereo, and a beechwood shift knob.
name: Carerra GT

description: The i8 is one of the wildest cars that BMW has released in recent memory. It boasts a head-turning, concept car-like design, butterfly doors, and a powerful plug-in hybrid powertrain that makes a combined 357 horsepower. This particular example is finished in Crystal White Pearl, and it touts reasonably low mileage, no modifications, and dry-climate California ownership from new. It also includes some great factor equipment, including the Pure Impulse World Package, 20-inch Style 625 wheels, LED headlights, and a Harman/Kardon sound system.
name: i8

description: This 1957 Mercedes-Benz 300SL is one of 1,858 roadsters manufactured during six years of production and is among the earliest of 554 first-year examples. Chassis 00094 is said to have been built on order for the last Shah of Irans twin sister, Princess Ashraf ol-Molouk Pahlavi, to whom it was dispatched on June 26, 1957. It was acquired in the early 1960s by aerospace industry pioneer Thomas Foster Hamilton and subsequently fitted with rally-oriented modifications including an aluminum roll hoop and a custom-fabricated instrument panel.
name: 300SL Roadster

description: The 992 Porsche 911 GT3 is one of the most exhilarating sports cars in the market, blending a thrilling driving character with exceptional performance and a high-revving naturally aspirated flat-6 engine. This particular GT3 is also fitted with the incredibly desirable 6-speed manual transmission, and it boasts some great factory equipment including a front suspension lift system, carbon fiber bucket seats, and a Bose surround sound system. It also shows just 2,100 miles on the odometer, and its mostly unmodified, with full-body paint protection film being the only change from stock
name: 911 GT3

description: The 992 Porsche 911 is an impressive and thrilling performance car and this one is really well equipped. It's a Carrera S model, so it has a muscular 443-horsepower flat-6 and it features the Premium and Sport packages, rear axle steering, a sport exhaust system, and a highly desirable (and very rare) aerokit. This 992 is also nearly unmodified, aside from paint protection film and tinted windows and it's finished in the stunning color combination of Shark Blue over a Bordeaux Red interior.
name: 911 Carrera S

description: Now this looks like a fantastic Porsche 911! Not only is it a powerful Targa 4S model with all-wheel drive and the show-stopping retractable targa top, it's also equipped with a long list desirable options, including the Premium and Sport Chrono packages, a front axle lift system, a leather interior with Chalk stitching, and adaptive cruise control. This 992 Targa is also unmodified, and it touts just 300 miles on the odometer so it's practically new and ready for the next enthusiast to call it their own.
name: 911 Targa 4S

description: Now this is a seriously impressive 911! Not only is it the powerful Carrera 4S with all-wheel drive, it's equipped with a 7-speed manual transmission and it's finished in an attractive white over black color combination. This 992 is also highly equipped with the Premium and Sport packages, 20-inch front and 21-inch rear Carrera Classic wheels, Porsche Dynamic Chassis Control (PDCC), a front axle lift system, heated front seats, and a heated steering wheel.
name: 911 Carrera 4S

description: The 992 Porsche 911 is a fantastic sports car that touts an iconic exterior design, excellent performance, and a nice interior. This particular Carrera Cabriolet is unmodified, and it comes equipped with the desirable Sport Chrono Package, heated and ventilated front seats, and Porsche crests on the headrests plus a great color combination, with the red roof perfectly fitting the silver exterior.
name: 911 Carrera Cabriolet

description: The Porsche 718 Cayman GT4 is one of the most exhilarating cars on the market today, as it offers a truly fantastic combination of performance, acceleration, and incredible steering and handling capabilities. This particular GT4 touts a 6-speed manual transmission, low mileage, and the desirable Porsche Ceramic Composite Brakes.
name: 718 Cayman GT4

description: The Porsche 718 Cayman GTS 4.0 is a seriously thrilling sports car that sits just below the GT4 in the Cayman lineup and it's phenomenally well-balanced, yet not overly harsh on the road. This particular GTS 4.0 is equipped with the desirable 6-speed manual transmission, and it touts low mileage, with just 3,000 miles on the odometer. It's also nicely equipped with the Premium and GTS Interior packages, and it hasn't been significantly modified.
name: 718 Cayman GTS

description: I love the 718 Boxster Spyder, as it combines the fun of top-down motoring with the driving thrills of a Cayman GT4 including the fantastic 4.0-liter naturally aspirated flat-6 engine with 414 horsepower. This particular Boxster Spyder is finished in a gorgeous Chalk over red and black color combination, and it touts some great equipment like the Spyder Classic Interior Package, 20-inch alloy wheels, heated seats, a heated multifunction steering wheel, and a Bose Surround Sound system.
name: 718 Boxster Spyder

description: he Cayman GT4 RS is one of the most exhilarating cars on the market today, offering a truly fantastic combination of performance, acceleration, and incredible steering and handling capabilities, along with additional power over the standard GT4. This particular GT4 RS features the desirable Weissach Package that adds a LOT of carbon fiber exterior trim, titanium tailpipes, a carbon fiber airbox and air intakes, and specific interior trim and it's equipped with the Light Design and Chrono packages, 20-inch magnesium wheels painted in Satin Indigo Blue, LED headlights with PDLS+, and a front axle lift system.
name: 718 Cayman GT4RS

description: The E36 M3 is an iconic BMW that has established its status as a modern classic and well-kept examples have become highly prized by enthusiasts. This particular M3 is a coupe that has some great benefits, like a 5-speed manual transmission, 17-inch Style 23 wheels, a stunning Estoril Blue Metallic over Magma color combination, and reasonably low mileage. It also boasts some desirable Dinan modifications including engine software, an axle-back exhaust, and lowering springs.
name: M3 Coupe
